content.step1: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9-inch round pan, line bottom with parchment paper. In a large bowl, sift together 1¾ cups flour, 1 cup sugar, ¾ cup cocoa, 1 tsp baking soda, ½ tsp baking powder, and pinch of salt. Mix until uniform.
content.step2: In a separate bowl, whisk 1 cup milk, ½ cup melted butter, 2 eggs, 2 tsp vanilla, and 1 tsp white vinegar. Combine wet ingredients into dry mixture, stirring until smooth. The vinegar reacts with baking soda, creating light, airy batter.
content.step3: Pour batter into prepared pan, smoothing top with spatula. Tap lightly on counter to release air bubbles. Let batter rest for 5 minutes; this allows gluten to relax, ensuring a tender crumb. Avoid opening oven door during baking.
content.step4: Bake 30-35 minutes. Check doneness by inserting a toothpick; it should come out clean or with a few crumbs. For extra moistness, brush the top with ¼ cup milk after removing from oven and allow to cool 10 minutes.
content.step5: Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes, then invert onto wire rack. Spread ½ cup chocolate ganache over the top, letting it set slightly before slicing. This ganache adds rich flavor and glossy finish.
content.step6: Serve slices with whipped cream or fresh berries for contrast. Store leftovers in airtight container at room temperature for up to 3 days, or refrigerate and enjoy within a week. Enjoy your homemade chocolate delight!
